<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-09T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-09T15:00:00-05:00" n="819" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11 G 93/1184: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-09T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                        1921—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>7. Your 21 July 3, 10 a.m.</p>
                        <p>You may defer action on Department’s 6, June 28th, 5 p.m., until such
                            time as in your judgment you can present it effectively.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>